          ],
          "parameters": {
            "width": 480,
            "height": 848,
            "content": "## Replicated Support Bundles → Snowflake\n\n### How it works\n\n1. The workflow starts with a weekly schedule trigger.\n2. It clears the Snowflake table for support bundles.\n3. Support bundles data is retrieved via an HTTP request.\n4. The retrieved data is split and manually mapped.\n5. The mapped data is updated in the Snowflake database.\n\n### Setup steps\n\n- [ ] Ensure Snowflake database credentials are correctly set up.\n- [ ] Ensure Replicated API credentials are configured for the HTTP request.\n- [ ] Schedule the trigger for the desired interval.\n\n### Customization\n\nYou can adjust the scheduling frequency to match your data processing needs."
          },
          "typeVersion": 1
        },
